              release: { tr: "Bucket policy'leri yazılmış (storage.objects RLS): <code>create policy &quot;own files&quot; on storage.objects for all using (bucket_id = 'avatars' and auth.uid()::text = (storage.foldername(name))[1])</code>. Resumable upload (büyük dosya) <code>upload(path, file, { upsert: true, contentType, cacheControl })</code> ile progress callback'i; image transformation <code>getPublicUrl(path, { transform: { width: 256 } })</code> ile. Public URL'lerde <strong>signed URL</strong> alternatifi (kısıtlı süre + access) hassas dosyalar için kullanılıyor.", en: "Bucket policies are written against storage.objects via RLS: <code>create policy &quot;own files&quot; on storage.objects for all using (bucket_id = 'avatars' and auth.uid()::text = (storage.foldername(name))[1])</code>. Resumable upload (large files) is done with <code>upload(path, file, { upsert: true, contentType, cacheControl })</code> and progress callback; image transformation uses <code>getPublicUrl(path, { transform: { width: 256 } })</code>. For sensitive files, <strong>signed URLs</strong> (time-limited access) are used instead of public URLs." }
